<!-- Node: "In Soviet Russia Videos Play Half-Life." -->
<div class="body_box_header">In Soviet Russia Videos Play Half-Life.</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/31" title="View user profile.">mazemaster</a> on Wednesday, June 9, 2004 - 21:01</small><br /><br />
Ever wanted to add a working TV set to your map? Now you can.<br />
<br />
 <a href="http://www.bits.bris.ac.uk/randomnine/projects/avikit/">AviKit</a> has released a mod <a href="http://www.bits.bris.ac.uk/randomnine/projects/avikit/avikit.zip">code kit</a> to allow .avi playback in your Half-Life mod. This is not some kludgy hack, this is real-time video playback on map objects in Half-Life. <a href="http://collective.valve-erc.com/index.php?news=1086730872-55251400">More info</a> is available at the <a href="http://collective.valve-erc.com">VERC</a>. <a href="http://www.bits.bris.ac.uk/randomnine/projects/avikit/akhl1.jpg">Screenshot</a>.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/login" >Login</a> or <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/register" >Register</a> to post comments &middot; <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/295" title="Read the rest of this posting." class="read-more"><b>Read more</b></a>
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Method's Turf" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Method's Turf</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2" title="View user profile.">G.A.R.D.</a> on Tuesday, June 8, 2004 - 00:44</small><br /><br />
RUST | gamedesign.net officially launched <a href="http://method.gamedesign.net">Method's Turf</a>. The first new gamedesign.net website that contains information and screenshots on the unofficial sequel for Kingpin, entitled <b>Kingpin:Final Crime</b>. The new site contains interviews with Xatrix (the people who made the original Kingpin), Kingpin Tutorials, Kingpin Levels and all sorts of Kingpin Related Material.<br />
<br />
<b>Who's Method</b><br />
<br />
Method is a talented level designer for Quake-Engine based games, particularly Kingpin (a game developed by Xatrix Entertainment Inc.) Method is a moderator on several RUST forums, including Kingpin, Radiant and the soon to be released Doom 3. Recently Method joined RUST and has contributed greatly to the news and content here at RUST.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/login" >Login</a> or <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/register" >Register</a> to post comments &middot; <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/294" title="Read the rest of this posting." class="read-more"><b>Read more</b></a>
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Code Locks in Half-Life" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Code Locks in Half-Life</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2" title="View user profile.">G.A.R.D.</a> on Monday, June 7, 2004 - 20:05</small><br /><br />
Sebastiannielsen has just posted a tutorial on the RUST website called <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/book/view/290">Code Locks</a>. Several techniques exist to make doors with code locks, but I think this is by far the easiest and most exciting method todate. Sebastiannielsen points out that the code locks will be cool in multiplayer maps, where the developer can have a "code" to enter a protect-room (full with weapons). Imagine a button to open a door with lava under all the other players. Why not a turret or use your imagination! Check out Sebastiannielsen's <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/book/view/290">Code Lock Tutorial</a>
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/login" >Login</a> or <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/register" >Register</a> to post comments &middot; <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/293" title="Read the rest of this posting." class="read-more"><b>Read more</b></a>
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Human Head Studios Hiring" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Human Head Studios Hiring</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2157" title="View user profile.">method</a> on Monday, June 7, 2004 - 19:06</small><br /><br />
Human Head Studios, Incorporated is looking for an animator to add to their collection of heads.  This is a full time, on-site position with benefits for a project using the DOOM 3 Engine.<br><br>

In order to be considered for this job, they require that you be able to demonstrate the following:<br><br>

1. Thorough understanding of animation fundamentals<br>including posing, timing, and character weight.<br>
2. Be able to rig character models for animation<br>
3. Working technical knowledge of Maya Animator.<br>
4. Willing to accept direction and work well under pressure.<br>
5. Self motivated and a desire to work with a team.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/login" >Login</a> or <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/register" >Register</a> to post comments &middot; <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/291" title="Read the rest of this posting." class="read-more"><b>Read more</b></a>
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Quake 4 won't be shown on QuakeCon this year" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Quake 4 won't be shown on QuakeCon this year</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2157" title="View user profile.">method</a> on Sunday, June 6, 2004 - 03:11</small><br /><br />
<a href = "http://www.planetquake.com/">PlanetQuake</a> got news about QuakeCon 2004. Todd Hollenshead (Id Software CEO) said that they won't be showing Quake 4, which is being developed by Raven Software with Id Software's supervision, on QuakeCon this year. They're happy with what they've done so far, but they want to make sure it's perfect before showing it to the public.<br />
Read full article <a href = "http://money.cnn.com/2004/06/04/commentary/game_over/column_gaming/index.htm">here</a>.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/login" >Login</a> or <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/register" >Register</a> to post comments
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Interplay offices closed by state officials" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Interplay offices closed by state officials</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2157" title="View user profile.">method</a> on Sunday, June 6, 2004 - 03:00</small><br /><br />
Gamespot got current news on Interplay. The Orange County Register reports that California labor investigators have shut down the publisher.<br />
<i><br />
"The company has not shut down. [The state] can’t do that. It can only let me not let employees work," Herve Caen said.<br />
</i><br />
Read full article <a href = "http://www.gamespot.com/news/2004/06/04/news_6100019.html">here</a>.
<br /><br />
