<!-- Node: "QuakeCon 2004 is coming!" -->
<div class="body_box_header">QuakeCon 2004 is coming!</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2157" title="View user profile.">method</a> on Friday, June 4, 2004 - 19:16</small><br /><br />
The 9th annual QuakeCon video game festival and tournament storms into town August 12-15 at the Gaylord Texan Resort & Convention Center in Grapevine, Texas. This annual fan pilgrimage to the largest, most awe-inspiring North American LAN event will be a four day adrenaline-pumping party with 5,000 of your closest friends.<br />
For additional info visit <a href = "http://www.idsoftware.com">Id Software</a> or head over to <a href = "http://www.quakecon.org/">QuakeCon</a> for all the details.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/login" >Login</a> or <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/register" >Register</a> to post comments
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "DOOM Movie" -->
<div class="body_box_header">DOOM Movie</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2157" title="View user profile.">method</a> on Friday, June 4, 2004 - 19:02</small><br /><br />
Todd Hollenshead (Id Software CEO) revealed that Warner Brothers, who had the right to the DOOM movie, passed on the option of making it. DOOM's movie license has been picked up by Universal Pictures now. The movie's script is based on DOOM 3, which is as stated by <a href = "http://www.darkhorizons.com/news04/040604d.php">Dark Horizons</a> will be shipped on July 15th.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/login" >Login</a> or <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/register" >Register</a> to post comments
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Interplay out of business?" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Interplay out of business?</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2157" title="View user profile.">method</a> on Friday, June 4, 2004 - 18:09</small><br /><br />
After Interplay's financial problems, there was a few rumors that their office is closing and they're going out of business.<br />
<br />
<i>Yesterday, <a href = "http://www.gamespot.com">GameSpot</a> talked with the surprisingly affable Caen, who denied the end was nigh for Interplay. His proof? "You can see our stock is trading, so we're still here," said Caen.</i><br />
<br />
So there's still a hope for Kingpin and Fallout fans to see a sequel to their favorite games. Read full article on <a href = "http://www.gamespot.com/news/2004/06/04/news_6099957.html">GameSpot</a>.
<br /><br />
